Network Troubleshooting

When network errors occur, follow this systematic diagnostic approach:

## Error Classification
- ECONNREFUSED → Check if service is running on target port
- ECONNRESET → Check firewall, proxy middleware
- ETIMEDOUT → Check routing, network reachability
- ENOTFOUND → Check DNS resolution
- SSL/TLS errors → Check certificate chain and validity
- HTTP 403/407 → Check auth, proxy credentials
- HTTP 502/503/504 → Server-side issue, retry

## Diagnostic Commands
1. Connectivity: `ping <host>`, `curl -v telnet://<host>:<port>`
2. DNS: `nslookup <host>`, `nslookup <host> 8.8.8.8`
3. Proxy: Check HTTP_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY env vars
4. SSL: `openssl s_client -connect <host>:443 -showcerts`
5. HTTP: `curl -vvv https://<host>/<path>`

## Common Fixes
- npm timeout: `npm config set registry https://registry.npmmirror.com`
- pip timeout: `pip config set global.index-url https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple`
- git fail: `git config --global http.proxy http://127.0.0.1:7890`
- DNS fail: Switch to 8.8.8.8, flush cache
- SSL fail: Update CA certificates, check cert chain
- Proxy not running: Start Clash/V2Ray, verify port
